                        <handDesc>
                            <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                                <date notBefore="1600" notAfter="1699" resp="bm:GrebTiss1935Codices">17th century</date>
                                <seg type="ink">Black, red.</seg>
                                <desc>The script exhibits the typical features of the period: the ascenders are parallel, the left stroke of ዘ is slightly curved;
                                    ሎ has no or very short linking line between the body of the letter and the loop; the upper parts of ቆ, ቶ, የ, ደ, ጸ are angular; ዐ is sharped.
                                </desc>
