                    <history>
                        <origin>
                            <origDate notBefore="1600" notAfter="1699"/>          
                            <note>The manuscript was written by a certain <persName role="scribe" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS14618SenaKr">Śǝna Krǝstos</persName> (mentioned on <locus target="#121v"/> and 
                                elsewhere) and belonged to several individuals, whose names are mentioned throughout the text:
                                firstly <persName role="owner" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS14619TaklaMa">Takla Māryām</persName>, then <persName role="owner" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS14620Zagiyo">Zagiyorgis</persName> 
                                (mentioned on <locus target="#62v #94v"/>), 
                                <persName role="owner" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS14621HabtaMi">Habta Mikāʾel</persName>, <persName role="owner" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS14622Yosef">Yosef</persName> and
                                finally <persName role="owner" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS14623Ermeyas">ʾErmǝyās</persName>, who is mentioned in the supplication formulas, e.g. on <locus target="#128r"/>. 
                                The latter also authored the <ref target="#a1">ownership note</ref> on <locus target="#131v"/>.
                            </note>
                        </origin>
                        <provenance>According to the account on the manuscripts’ provenance given by Eugène Tisserant, this manuscript is among those
                            acquired by <persName role="owner" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS4805Grebaut">Sylvain Grébaut</persName> in <date when="1925"/> with funds of
                            <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS14055SaintJ">Jean Saint</persName>. 
                            The manuscripts originated from Šawā (ʾAddis ʾAbabā, Dabra Libānos, Dabra Bǝrhān),
                            Goǧǧām (Dimā Giyorgis, Marṭula Māryām, Dabra Warq) and Bagemdǝr (Gondar, ʾAzazo Takla Hāymānot) and very few from Tǝgrāy.
                        </provenance>
                        <acquisition when="1928">The manuscript entered the library on <date>18 April 1928</date>.</acquisition>
                    </history>
